---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const updated = "June 26, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Pumkin"
  description="How Pumkin (Software For Humans) handles your data: what little we collect, why, and your rights."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="container legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      Pumkin is a product of <strong>Software For Humans, LLC</strong>, operated by Lewis LaBrie
      ("we", "us"). This policy explains what personal data we collect when you visit
      <a href="https://pumkin.app">pumkin.app</a>, why, and the rights you have over it. Questions:
      <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>
      The Pumkin desktop app runs entirely on your machine. Your prompts, your models, your
      files, and your agent runs never reach us — there is no Pumkin cloud and no telemetry on
      your agent activity. Pumkin is free, so there's no purchase and no payment data. The only
      personal data we ever hold is what you send us directly, such as a support email.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Email correspondence.</strong> If you email us for support, we keep that
        correspondence so we can help you and follow up.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Basic server logs.</strong> Our hosting provider may process standard technical
        data (such as IP address and request metadata) to serve the site securely. We do not use
        this for tracking or advertising.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we do NOT do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not run advertising or third-party tracking pixels on this site.</li>
      <li>We do not collect any data from inside the Pumkin desktop application.</li>
      <li>We do not sell or rent your personal data to anyone.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Where the software is distributed</h2>
    <p>
      Pumkin is downloaded from <strong>GitHub Releases</strong>. When you download it, GitHub
      processes your request under its own privacy terms; we don't receive your identity from those
      downloads.
    </p>

    <h2>Why we process it (legal bases)</h2>
    <p>
      We process support emails and keep that correspondence under our <strong>legitimate
      interests</strong> in supporting the software, and we process basic server logs under our
      legitimate interest in serving the site securely.
    </p>

    <h2>Who processes your data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — website hosting.</li>
      <li><strong>GitHub</strong> — hosting the source code and release downloads.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each operates under its own privacy terms. Some may process data outside your country; where
      that happens, appropriate safeguards (such as Standard Contractual Clauses) apply.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live (including under the EU/UK GDPR), you have the right to access,
      correct, delete, or export your personal data, and to object to or restrict certain
      processing. To exercise any of these, email <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>
      and we'll respond within a reasonable time. You also have the right to complain to your local
      data protection authority.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>Pumkin is a developer tool intended for adults. We do not knowingly collect data from children.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as the product evolves. Material changes will be reflected by the
      "last updated" date above.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Software For Humans, LLC — Virginia, United States. Email <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="legal-nav"><a href="/terms">Terms of Service →</a></p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 720px; padding-top: 3rem; padding-bottom: 4rem; }
  .legal h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal .updated { color: var(--brand-fg-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .legal h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-top: 2.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { line-height: 1.7; color: var(--brand-fg); }
  .legal p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .legal ul { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; padding-left: 1.4rem; }
  .legal li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal a { color: var(--brand-accent-quiet); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .legal-nav { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--brand-border); }
</style>
